article.description: James Anderson II had 19 points off the bench to carry North Alabama to a 78-58 win over Kennesaw State on Thursday night.
article.headline: Anderson leads North Alabama over Kennesaw State 78-58
article.linkText: Anderson leads North Alabama over Kennesaw State 78-58
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- James Anderson II had 19 points off the bench to carry North Alabama to a 78-58 win over Kennesaw State on Thursday night. Anderson II shot 4 for 6 from beyond the arc. Christian Agnew had 12 points and seven rebounds for North Alabama (9-11, 4-3 Atlantic Sun Conference). Jamari Blackmon added 11 points. C.J. Brim had 11 points, eight rebounds and eight assists. Tyler Hooker had 12 points for the Owls (1-18, 0-6), who have now lost 10 straight games. C.J. Washington added 11 points. Ugo Obineke had 10 points. North Alabama takes on NJIT on the road next Thursday. Kennesaw State faces Jacksonville at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
